ROMANCE of TROPANE
raw_affl: F. PAUL ANSBRO, M.D., is a native of Brooklyn, New York. He received the Bachelor of Arts degree from Holy Cross College and his medical degree from Marquette University. He was an enlisted man in U. S. Naval Aviation during 1917 to 1919. Dr. Ansbro is Director of Anesthesiology at St. Catherine's Hospital, Holy Family Hospital and St. Anthony Hospital, Brooklyn, attending anesthesiologist at Adelphi Hospital and consultant anesthesiologist at several other hospitals. He was formerly Assistant Clinical Professor of Anesthesiology at New York State University. He has spent 5 years in compiling data for a book on anatomy, physiology and pharmacology of the autonomic nervous system, and hopes to have it completed in the not too distant future. His hobbies are history and chemistry. Dr. and Mrs. Ansbro have 2 sons, 2 daughters and 4 grandchildren.; St. Catherine's Hospital.

He has spent 5 years in compiling data for a book on anatomy, physiology and pharmacology of the autonomic nervous system, and hopes to have it completed in the not too distant future. His hobbies are history and chemistry. Dr. and Mrs. Ansbro have 2 sons, 2 daughters and 4 grandchildren.; St. Catherine's Hospital.

title: ROMANCE of TROPANE
raw_affl: Now Director of Anesthesiology, Wyoming Valley General Hospital, Wilkes Barre, Pennslyvania.; WILBERT E. HERNANDEZ, M.D., was born in Progreso, Yucatan, Mexico. He received his medical degree from The Hahnemann Medical College of Philadelphia in 1941. He also received training in anesthesiology at St. Catherine's Hospital, Brooklyn. He was a Captain in the Medical Corps and served from May to December 1951 at the U. S. Army Hospital, Fort Sill, Oklahoma and from January 1952 to March 1953 at Rodriguez Army Hospital, San Juan, Puerto Rico. Dr. Hernandez is Chief of the Department of Anesthesia at Wyoming Valley Hospital, Wilkes-Barre, Pennsylvania and Pittston Hospital, Pittston, Pennsylvania; attending anesthesiologist to the Veterans Administration Hospital, Wilkes-Barre, Pennsylvania, and Secretary of the Medical Staff, Wyoming Valley Hospital. A Certificate of Appreciation was given him by the American Society of Anesthesiologists for a scientific exhibit entitled “Evaluation of Promethazine for Anesthesia.” Fishing and stamp collecting are his hobbies. Dr. Hernandez and his wife, Jayne, have 2 daughters.

His military service was spent in the United States Navy overseas in the North Atlantic, Mediterranean, North Africa and France. Dr. Lear is adjunct anesthesiologist at Jewish Hospital, Brooklyn, and assistant visiting anesthesiologist at Jewish Hospital, Brooklyn, Assistant visiting anesthesiologist at Queens General Hospital, Jamaica, New York, and holds a teaching appointment at State University as Clinical Instructor in Anesthesiology. raw_affl: F. W. SCHUELER, PH.D., is a native of Ft. Collins, Colorado. He obtained the bachelor of arts degree and the master of arts degree from Colorado University at Boulder, and his doctor of philosophy degree from the University of Chicago. Dr. Schueler received the Ebert prize in pharmaceutical chemistry in 1955 and the J. J. Abel prize in pharmacology in 1956. He is Professor and Chairman of the Department of Pharmacology at Tulane University Medical School, New Orleans, Louisiana. His special interests are music and mathematics. Dr. Schueler and his wife, Julia, are the parents of a daughter and a son.
